This paper deals with computer vision and image classification using convolutional neural nets, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The addition of a side branch to convert the ROI mask into an attention map involves machine learning techniques, which could also place this paper under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of contextual cues from the background could also involve artificial intelligence techniques, which could place this paper under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The evaluation of the method using datasets could also involve multimedia techniques, which could place this paper under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of attention maps to focus on specific regions of an image could also involve information retrieval techniques, which could place this paper under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
